Nollywood superstars Mercy Johnson-Okojie, Jim Iyke, Zubby Micheal, Jide Kosoko and Adedimeji Lateef are set to star in a Vincent Okonkwo-produced ghetto comedy titled “Passport.” The film, directed by Dimeji Ajibola, chronicles two characters, Oscar and Funke, wallowing in loneliness as they search for some excitement in their lives. To recover his passport, Oscar needs help from a tomboy who lives in the ghetto. He must work with her or miss a flight to a job interview that could change his life. Following the completion of the principal shooting, Okonkwo took to the Instagram page to appreciate the actors and other crew members involved in the film’s production, as well as share some behind-the-scenes photos. - Advertisement - Captioning his post, the filmmaker wrote: “When I decided to produce #passportthemovie I knew it won’t be easy considering the quality of cast and today we wrapped against all odds thanks to God almighty we made a beautiful star-studded movie.   Rosy Meurer shares son’s first day in school     Teni bags endorsement deal with Samsung     Woli Agba laments hike in fish price   “I want to say a big thank u to @mercyjohnsonokojie who took time away from family engagement to bring her character to life. In fact, I couldn’t have picked a better choice than her for this lead role. “@zubbymichael my brother and friend for proving my selection decision right once again this is now the 3rd time working and I know it can only get better. “@jim.iyke for pushing himself beyond the limit to deliver exceptionally as the lead character. “@adedimejilateef am convinced I found a team player thank u, my brother. “@iamnasboi & @ememufot for giving more depth to the characters. “@princejidekosoko my Nollywood daddy thank u soo much. “@emeneks @caroline_igben @stephendamian @izzydahniel @tubyunic & @bukiea_d thank u all for bringing your A game to this project.”